column5: Well here it is the first walleye or pickeral for Joey's Team #2 a 29" and I thought that I should get this up and tomorrow being the last day of ice fishing on the Bay of Quinte I will try to beat it if possible.        Regards, Sam
That's awesome Sam,Congrats!!!!!  Bassman

WTG Sam... I see what you were doing on the weekend bringing me to the fish wastelands  just kidding with ya... But way to go and glad to see that you actually got a chance to go out and catch something this season...
thats a hog
That thing is fat. Full of eggs ?
....*pores over members list for looking for someone named DT10Sam*  Alright I concede, seems he's been an outstanding member and huge contributor to OFC past and present. NIce fish Sam.
Congrats, great looking fish!!!  One of the best fish posted this ice fishing season.
Oh Sam, You Da Man!!!!  Thank you Sweetie.  This will put us off to a great start  Thanks  Joey
nice fish!!
WTG Sam.....of course you know I'm pissed that you're not on my team....  Thanks for those great pics!
YEAH!!!!! wtg sam.........Thats a real nice looking fish you caught they're...  Go team 2 go!!
WHOA!!! Nice WALLEYE!!!  You're absolutely sure it didn't come out of your freezer right??? LOL....j/k  Great fish!! Great job!!!
WTG Sam, awesome pickeral !!  Your always working to help everyone else get the bigguns, so it's good to see you hooking up too.
That sux!  Congrats on the nice Wall-ice Sam!
Sam, can I have that one? Team 5 needs it for bait!  Nice fish Sam!!!!!!
Beauty, WTG...
I am with TJSA, but only because hes my captian though. (secretly I am jealous and wish I was you) o shoot did I say that outloud???  Art

Higuys,  I really know that you do not mean all of this hatred this is the fun we are going to have.  I do know that there was a household last night that had an extremely difficult time with it though. LOL  Just imagine being in Joey's home and seeing her walk around the home with a grin from ear to ear and not saying anything.  Aaahhhhh yes then there is Tybo who is eating crow as a daily meal right about now.LOL I sure hope he uses spices it would taste better.  Regards, Sam

In all the time I have been on the board I think that is the first time I have seen you holding a fish in a picture Sam! (and a huge one at that!)  Great to see that you are getting out fishing, way to kick things into high gear for Team #2 with that Walleye!  Talk to ya soon, Tony
Sam, I thought Tybo was singing a beatles song, cause everytime I mentioned your entry for our team, he just kept going, "yeah, yeah, yeah!"  Awesome.  Joey
The recipe for CROW.  One crow. Finely diced onion. Salt,pepper and garlic. Bake until flaky.  Nice fish Sam.
GREAT fish Sam...but Team 7's gonna wait till fall to beat that baby!
That walleye sure is a beauty. Go team go!
Nice big hog there Sam!!   Bly
